  "text": "We have evaluated the effect of ER accumulation of ZAAT on apoptosis in HEK293 cells using the ER stress agonist thapsigargin and MAAT and ZAAT transgenes [CITATION_1] . We found that, similar to treatment with thapsigargin, expression of ZAAT, but not MAAT, induced cleavage of procaspase-4 and downstream executioner caspases. Given the poorly defined role of caspase-4 in ER stress-induced apoptosis which tends to be stimulus and cell type specific we decided to investigate its role in ZAAT-induced cell death. To evaluate this we knocked-down caspase-4 protein expression in HEK293 cells. Interestingly this did not promote cell survival in ZAAT expressing cells, nor did it inhibit ZAAT-induced caspase-7 activation. These data led us to conclude that caspase-4 is not at the apex of the ZAAT/ER-induced apoptotic signalling pathway and is not essential for ER-mediated apoptosis in HEK293 cells.",
